body_html:
The tag file has no purpose other than displaying a version number at
startup. The missing tag file can be ignored.
On Fri, Aug 5, 2016 at 9:25 AM QiHong Lu notifications@github.com wrote:

I also had the same TAG issue:
WARNING:tensorflow:IOError [Errno 2] No such file or directory:
'/Users/Qihong/anaconda/envs/tensorflow/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/tensorboard/TAG'
on path
/Users/Qihong/anaconda/envs/tensorflow/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/tensorboard/TAG

WARNING:tensorflow:Unable to read TensorBoard tag

michaelosthege said that this can be resolved by downloading that TAG
file, but can someone explain what's the purpose of that TAG file? What is
the number in the file?
